Control over how the carousel takes over the screen can mostly be defined in a css file. Setting min-height on the .fullscreen-carousel-content elements will prevent them from shrinking to far vertically when the browser is very short, and setting max-height on the .fullscreen-carousel itself will prevent the area from becoming to long in the case that the browser is stretched very tall.
